cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with unsupervised word translation from non-parallel inter-lingual corpora. It also involves the use of neural network methods and language models. 

It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the use of iterative matching methods and deep adversarial approaches. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of machine learning techniques to solve a natural language processing problem. 

It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it involves the use of image alignment techniques to align word distributions. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves the task of word translation, which is relevant to information retrieval systems that need to process multilingual content.
